label.value: dietary approaches to stop hypertension diet

value.value: Is a diet designed to prevent and control high blood pressure. It promotes consumption of fruits, vegetables, whole grains, nuts, legumes, lean meat, fish, poultry and low-fat dairy products, and the inclusion of micronutrients and the reduction of sodium in the diet to about 1500 mg/day. It is limited in sugar-sweetened foods and beverages, red meat, and added fats.
